Police have arrested a suspect believed to be behind a fake money printing syndicate in Eldoret town. Fake currencies including dollars, sterling pounds and Kenyan shilling notes valued at over Sh45.8 million as well as money printing machines were recovered. Uasin Gishu police commander Johstone Ipara who led the operation said officers have been trailing the suspect identified as Allan Kipruto through the weekend following a tip?off by the members of the public. According to Ipara, several farmers and traders in the county have fallen victim of the fake money syndicate.